Option A — Deploy to Render (easiest)

Create a Render account (render.com).

Create a new Web Service and connect your GitHub repo.

For environment, set build & start commands (or use Docker image from Docker Hub).

Add environment variables (MONGODB_URI, JWT_SECRET) in Render dashboard.

Deploy — Render will build and serve your app, give you a URL.

Option B — VPS (Ubuntu) with Docker Compose

Provision a server (DigitalOcean droplet, AWS EC2).

Install Docker & Docker Compose.

git clone your repo on the server.

Put .env file on server with production values and JWT_SECRET.

Run:


docker-compose up -d --build
